  "text": "Using the Rayleigh quotient for the coupled vibrations, the squares of the natural frequencies of the diaphragm in a vacuum are proportional to the ratio between the maximum potential energy of the diaphragm V D and its kinetic energy T D [CITATION_1] . Due to the mode shapes of the diaphragm vibration in constant with a fluid are assumed to be equal to those of the diaphragm vibration in a vacuum, the squares of the natural frequencies in fluid are proportional to the ratio between the maximum potential energy of the diaphragm V D and the sum of the kinetic energies of both the diaphragm T D and the fluid T F . Therefore, we can obtain",
